snippet: James Wilson, 18, made his debut for United with two goals in a 3-1 victory over Hull in the Premier League on Tuesday, keeping alive the team’s chances of qualifying for the Europa League.
abstract: Manchester United beats Hull, 3-1, keeping alive team's hopes of qualifying for Europa League; other soccer news noted.
lead_paragraph: James Wilson, 18, made his debut for United with two goals in a 3-1 victory over Hull in the Premier League on Tuesday, keeping alive the team’s chances of qualifying for the Europa League.
